{
  "texts": [
    "Achieving favorable treatment outcomes and patient satisfaction in cases of facial asymmetry relies on accurate preoperative planning.",
    "This systematic review highlights the importance of precisely determining the MSP during diagnosis and treatment planning.",
    "Despite significant methodological variations across the included studies, the following conclusions can be drawn:",
    "Provided that stable landmarks are used, both cephalometric and morphometric methods for MSP construction are equally effective and offer the closest approximation to the true symmetrical MSP. 2.",
    "Among the various cephalometric and morphometric methods, a cephalometric MSP constructed using stable landmarks such as N-S and perpendicular to the FH plane provides optimal estimation of facial asymmetry."
  ]
}